1
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:13,640
It's all your fault.

2
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,280
I knew I'd get the blame again.

3
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:16,480
Enough.

4
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:18,520
I'll go check if the ground at the west end was touched.

5
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:20,040
Is that even necessary?

6
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:21,040
Brother, it's such a long way.

7
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:22,600
Why do you insist on making this trip?

8
00:00:25,360 --> 00:00:25,800
Look.

9
00:00:26,080 --> 00:00:27,480
The ground at the west end hasn't been touched.

10
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:29,040
Of course it hasn't been touched.

11
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:30,080
Because the jar we talked about...

12
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:31,960
...was buried at the east end of the village!

13
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:34,200
It's all your fault!

14
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,600
You couldn't even explain the rules clearly.

15
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:37,320
Sir.

16
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:39,000
I'll go ask Xiao Hua for help.

17
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:39,760
Go ahead.

18
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:40,440
Wait.

19
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:42,000
Did you tell Xiao Hua...

20
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,200
...that the jar is buried at the east end...

21
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,320
...or the west end?

22
00:00:44,440 --> 00:00:46,760
No need to mention burying the jar anymore.

23
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:48,880
It doesn't matter anyway.

24
00:00:50,080 --> 00:00:50,880
No way.

25
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:52,320
We're going to argue again.

26
00:00:57,760 --> 00:00:58,560
Have you been waiting long?

27
00:00:58,560 --> 00:00:59,320
No.

28
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:00,760
This is what I ran all over the mountain...

29
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:02,320
...to brew for you: Hundred-Flower Snakegrass Brew.

30
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:02,880
Taste it, quick.

31
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:07,080
How is it?

32
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:08,720
Tastes like a sleeping mat.

33
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:09,320
It's delicious.

34
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:10,320
Thank you, Brother Wei Qiao.

35
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,120
As long as you like it.

36
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:12,440
Um...

37
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:15,120
Actually, I have a favor to ask you.

38
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,200
What is it?

39
00:01:20,960 --> 00:01:21,560
What?

40
00:01:21,560 --> 00:01:22,320
There's a spy?

41
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:24,280
The Village Chief knows the way out.

42
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:26,320
Spread this news as fast as possible.

43
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:27,640
It will force them to make a move sooner.

44
00:01:28,440 --> 00:01:29,640
So exciting!

45
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:30,880
I promise to complete the mission.

46
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:34,400
My dad knows the way out. Keep it down!

47
00:01:34,760 --> 00:01:36,600
My dad knows the way out!

48
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:38,920
You're back.

49
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:40,440
Let's eat.

50
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:41,080
So many dishes.

51
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:41,880
Smells so good.

52
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:44,240
You've all worked hard.

53
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:45,320
Have some tea.

54
00:01:45,440 --> 00:01:46,440
Not at all, not at all.

55
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,480
Just in time, I'm thirsty. Thanks.

56
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:52,680
What special occasion is it today?

57
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:53,640
To have cooked so many good dishes?

58
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:55,200
Haven't you heard?

59
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,880
The Village Chief knows a secret passage.

60
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,800
We might be able to leave soon.

61
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,440
However...

62
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:04,960
some people...

63
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,240
...will have to part ways with everyone.

64
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,400
True.

65
00:02:09,640 --> 00:02:12,280
After all, some people have to go back to report back.

66
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:13,160
You...

67
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:13,880
Alright, alright.

68
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,520
Stop arguing, stop arguing.

69
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:16,760
Just eat your food.

70
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:31,400
Yu Tong...

71
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:32,760
You actually...

72
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:39,200
Don't move.

73
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:44,560
Don't hurt them.

74
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,120
Brother Yuwen.

75
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,520
I'm sorry.

76
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,120
We each serve our own master, that's all.

77
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:52,880
I won't hurt you all.

78
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:54,120
Now that it's come to this...

79
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:56,120
I just want to ask you one thing.

80
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:57,120
Did you really...

81
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:57,960
...never love me?

82
00:02:59,200 --> 00:02:59,640
I have to say...

83
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:01,200
...what are you thinking, kid?

84
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,200
This is the Third Princess of my Daye Kingdom.

85
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,560
You, a lowly Wei Kingdom Strategist...

86
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,640
...dare to be so impudent?

87
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,120
Congratulations, Princess.

88
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,160
The great undertaking is almost complete.

89
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,200
Dig up the jar.

90
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:17,640
Then let's leave immediately.

91
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:19,120
Let's go.

92
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:47,360
Princess

93
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,480
There's no Jar here either

94
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,000
We were tricked after all

95
00:03:58,640 --> 00:03:59,080
Brother

96
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:00,240
Do we keep digging?

97
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,000
You like digging?

98
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,000
Go dig yourself

99
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,400
Dig, dig

100
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:10,080
What kind of acting was that?

101
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:12,120
After I fell, you should have waited a bit before falling

102
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:12,880
What was my acting?

103
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:13,560
At least I had a process

104
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,320
You didn't even have a process

105
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:14,880
You just fell straight down

106
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:15,880
I thought you dropped dead

107
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:16,640
Who dropped dead?

108
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:17,400
You're the one who dropped dead

109
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:18,240
Your whole family dropped dead

110
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:19,760
Just in time, I'm thirsty

111
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,160
Thanks

112
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,760
I knew this method would force out the spy

113
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,200
I didn't expect it to really be her

114
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,680
Strategist

115
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:42,920
Look at the situation

116
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,200
And you're asking if she loves you?

117
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:45,160
Seriously

118
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:45,840
Enough

119
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:52,600
Tell me

120
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,880
That look in her eyes when she left

121
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,280
Was she reluctant to leave?

122
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,600
Strategist, have some dignity, will you?

123
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,640
She is a spy from the Daye Kingdom

124
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:02,320
Exactly

125
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:03,960
This has nothing to do with feelings

126
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:06,080
So, in this scheme...

127
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,040
Was I included too?

128
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:09,800
No

129
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,640
Then why didn't you tell me?

130
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:12,720
There was knockout drug in the tea

131
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,280
If I hadn't been on guard...

132
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,480
I would have fallen for it long ago

133
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,960
Isn't your martial arts skill so high?

134
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:17,960
You'd surely know

135
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,160
Right?

136
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,480
But you still should have told me

137
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,040
Stop arguing

138
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,040
Please, stop arguing

139
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,000
Argue, argue

140
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:23,880
Let them argue

141
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:24,680
Argue harder

142
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:25,960
If that's not enough, use knives

143
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,160
Stab, stab, come on

144
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:27,880
Stab right here

145
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,000
Save me from this misery

146
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,120
Now I'm the only single one

147
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,400
Strategist

148
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,760
You still have a chance

149
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,160
That there's a way out...

150
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,280
That news was fake

151
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:41,000
Maybe they'll come back in a bit

152
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,560
Then I'll go welcome her

153
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,360
Come back, come back

154
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,360
Bad news, bad news

155
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:47,960
What's wrong, Xiao Hua?

156
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:50,000
My dad said there really is a way out

157
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,400
Yesterday He Qi asked him to drink

158
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,160
He got drunk

159
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,640
And seems to have told He Qi

160
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:57,600
Yu Tong

161
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:58,920
Yu Tong

162
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:00,080
Wait for me here

163
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:00,640
Don't go anywhere

164
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:01,200
Okay

165
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,880
Chase, chase, chase

166
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,400
Back again?

167
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,280
Is it because of me?

168
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,200
Cut the crap

169
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,240
Where is the Jar?

170
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:20,640
Please tell her

171
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,680
The Jar is right in my heart

172
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,440
If she wants it, come and get it

173
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:25,400
Shameless

174
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:26,200
Princess

175
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,440
Tell him

176
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,800
I only want the Jar

177
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:29,920
Tell her

178
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:32,080
Taking the Jar will also take my heart

179
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,080
Tell him

180
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,880
Saying that only makes me sick

181
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:35,920
Tell her

182
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:36,960
Even disgust comes from the heart

183
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:38,040
If you take it, take it all

184
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:38,880
Tell him

185
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:40,280
Without the Jar, I'm not leaving

186
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:41,000
Tell her

187
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,480
I'm very happy she can stay

188
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,000
I like you. I hate you

189
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,200
Never seen anyone so disgusting

190
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:54,960
Yeah

191
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,080
This guy has no dignity left

192
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:19,920
Did you find the Jar?

193
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:21,280
No.

194
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:22,560
However,

195
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:23,720
Your Highness,

196
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:24,880
even without the Jar,

197
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:26,320
we can still go back and report.

198
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:28,280
Then I'll storm back with a thousand Elite troops.

199
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,320
We'll leave no stone unturned,

200
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,520
and we'll surely find the Jar.

201
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,640
Do you take them for fools?

202
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:34,560
If we leave, they won't stay put.

203
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:36,040
Well,

204
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:38,160
do you...

205
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,520
take us for fools?

206
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,080
Anyone with eyes

207
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,080
can see at a glance

208
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,560
that you're not staying for the Jar.

209
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:46,320
You're just after that lousy Strategist guarding it.

210
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:47,720
What nonsense are you talking?

211
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,520
I've already told you,

212
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,880
it's just to get the Jar.

213
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,000
There is no other reason.

214
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,520
I mean what I say.

215
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:54,680
You said it.

216
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,800
How are you talking to me?

217
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:57,800
Fine, then.

218
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,160
You... you get some rest.
